							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ajgoldmann/"><img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/62efbf70c1bcd5a6dc661c295f592126?s=100&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/62efbf70c1bcd5a6dc661c295f592126?s=200&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-100 photo' height='100' width='100' decoding='async'/></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/ajgoldmann/">A.J. Goldmann</a></h6>
										A.J. Goldmann is an American writer and critic based in Munich and Berlin. Over the past two decades, he has written about European and Jewish art, culture and society for the <em>New York Times</em>, <em>The Wall Street Journal</em>, <em>The Atlantic</em>, <em>The New Republic</em> and the <em>Forward</em>.																			</div>
