ers and Forgery</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">January 14, 2025</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/bradfordmorrow/">Bradford Morrow</a></span></div></li><li><div class="post_circle_thumb"><a href="https://crimereads.com/scott-turow-presumed-interview/"><img class="lazy" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lazy-sq.png" data-src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2025/01/Turow-Scott-2024-Audrey-Snow-Owen-2-150x150.jpg" alt=""></a></div><div class="text-container"><strong class="title"><a href="https://crimereads.com/scott-turow-presumed-interview/">Presume Nothing: Scott Turow on the Rule of Law, Race, and Revisiting Rusty Sabich</a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">January 14, 2025</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/johnvaleri/">John B. Valeri</a></span></div></li><li><div class="post_circle_thumb"><a href="https://crimereads.com/how-to-know-if-your-idea-is-a-novel-or-a-screenplay-and-why-thrillers-make-great-tv/"><img class="lazy" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/plugins/lb-content-widgets/img/lazy-sq.png" data-src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/04/writing-150x150.jpg" alt=""></a></div><div class="text-container"><strong class="title"><a href="https://crimereads.com/how-to-know-if-your-idea-is-a-novel-or-a-screenplay-and-why-thrillers-make-great-tv/">How To Know If Your Idea Is a Novel or a Screenplay, and Why Thrillers Make Great TV </a></strong><span class="post_attribute center"><span class="post_detail_date">January 14, 2025</span> by <a href="https://crimereads.com/author/sandrachwialkowska/">Sandra Chwialkowska</a></span></div></li></ul></li>
